2.1 Overview of Streams

➡ A stream is a sequence of data you can read from (Input) or write to (Output).

➡ Streams are abstract - the data may come from a file, network socket, memory,
  or another program.

➡ Streams are usually one-directional (read or write).

➡ You often wrap a low-level stream (like FileInputStream) with higher-level filters
  (buffering, conversion, object serialization, etc.) to add features.


